<h1>Curtis James</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.notkindacool.com/now">notkindacool.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Brighton
East Sussex
United Kingdom
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Photographer and ethnographer at Fieldwork.  Photographer at Beyond Work (personal photo project).
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I uncover and share stories about work for people and companies.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I’ve spent many years working for myself, trying to help companies fix themselves. I realised a few years ago that something was missing, and that was a clear picture of work and culture. Using photography, listening and other ethnographic tools, I want to inspire us all to make the world of work a respectful, humane and kind place that rewards people with more than just money.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
The goodness of nearly everything I do now comes from the simple idea of getting out of the way of myself. This idea came from some acting coaching I’ve been having recently.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Keith Johnstone - Impro
</p>

